US authorities forced Musk to leave the post of Chairman of the Board of Tesla
American businessman Elon Musk will leave the position of Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Tesla founded by him at the request of the US authorities.
To settle the claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $ 20 million.
According to CNBC, a pre-trial agreement with the department allows Musk to remain at the head of the Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $ 20 million and leave the post of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and at least for three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed to his place.
It is specified that the agreement still must be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the US Securities and Exchange Commission accused Musk of misleading shareholders with a statement about the availability of sufficient funds to redeem shares of this company and sued the entrepreneur.
We are talking about the publication of the businessman on Twitter, where he announced his desire to buy Tesla shares at $ 420 apiece, but did not do it.
After the tweet, the company's shares grew by almost 11%.
The head of the British foreign Ministry compared the EU with the Soviet Union and the prison
British Foreign Secretary Jeremy Hunt compared the European Union to the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of capturing community member states.
With such a statement, the diplomat made at the Congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
According to the Daily Mail, in this way Hunt commented on the difficulties in the negotiation process on Brexit.
What happened to faith in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not allow anyone to leave.
The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from community to prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who wants to escape from captivity,” the minister said.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the European Union will only aggravate the crisis, notes Gazeta.ru.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that the Brexit talks had reached an impasse.
So she commented on the results of the informal summit of the European Union in Salzburg.
The Brexit decision was made in 2016 following the results of the referendum.
It is expected that the withdrawal of the United Kingdom should take place before April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue will be complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
In addition, the question of the Irish border remains open.
