Elon Musk is forced to leave the post of head of Tesla’s board of directors
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and Tesla founder Elon Musk have settled their dispute in the fraud case.
This is reported by CNBC News.
According to the channel, as part of the agreements reached, Musk will have to leave the post of head of the board of directors of Tesla.
At the same time, the commission allowed Musk to retain the post of head of Tesla.
As noted, the founder of Tesla will also have to pay an administrative fine of $ 20 million.
A similar amount will be collected from Tesla.
At the same time, the money will be distributed among the affected investors.
In addition, the company must appoint two independent directors.
Elon Musk is an American entrepreneur, included in the list of the 50 richest people in the planet according to Forbes magazine.
He is the head of SpaceX’s space corporation, Neuralink’s neurotechnology company and Tesla’s electric car developer, and the publisher of Paypal.
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission has previously sued Tesla CEO Elon Musk because of his tweeted on a possible redemption of the company.
Last month, Musk announced plans to make Tesla a private company and buy out all shares on the stock exchange at a fixed price of $420.
The cost of the $ 420 stock was set allegedly “due to the importance of this number in the culture of marijuana”, Bloomberg reported earlier, citing co-director of the commission’s security department, Stephen Peikin.
At the same time, Elon Musk subsequently abandoned his plans to buy off the shares.
Commenting on the lawsuit filed against him by the US Securities and Exchange Commission, the businessman said that he considers the accusations of fraud unfounded, and added that he is very disappointed and saddened by these claims.
“Honesty is the most important value of my life, and the facts will prove that I didn’t break it in any way,” the businessman said in an interview with CNBC.
At the same time, in August, a group of Tesla shareholders filed a class action lawsuit against the Mask, complaining about the financial losses suffered.
The plaintiffs claimed that the businessman’s posts brought them losses.
In particular, one of the shareholders said that the businessman’s tweets were misled, because of which Tesla stock sellers were forced to buy securities at artificially inflated prices in order to cover their positions.
Also, other plaintiffs noted that the careless statements of Elon Musk led to sharp fluctuations in the course.
In September, Elon Musk accused the head of the research company Citron Research.
Meanwhile, if Musk could not settle his dispute with the US Securities and Exchange Commission, he would be threatened with suspension from the management of the company and even a prison.
This, in particular, was stated by CNBC former chairman of the commission Harvey Pitt.
Musk is a “good guy who doesn’t know how to drive a car company.”
