“The arrival of such technologies is a unique thing, it is a colossal good.
This is an explosive growth of medical technologies, it is an improvement in the quality of life and infrastructure.
But there is also a second side.
The development of nature-like technologies is actually a technological reproduction of wildlife systems.
There is a flip side - purposeful interference in human life.
There are always risks.
There was a car - people began to die under the wheels.
But cars are still used.
The dual nature of technology at once.
I am creating a medical new technology, and at the same time I can create weapons of mass destruction, ”the scientist quotes REN TV.
